        <p>The first part of my submitted 3-part Web Technologies unit assignments.</p>
        <p>The challenge was to design a visually attractive multi-page website using strictly W3C standards compliant XHTML1.0 and CSS2.1. As little graphics as possible was to be used as graphics work would not be assessed at this point.</p>
        <p>Using CSS, I set up the framework to allow for a transitioning background effect. As the user scrolls down the page, the background image changes from black circles to grey circles. This would later be built upon in the next assignment to transition from one image to a completely different one.</p>
        <p>A timeline was also made for the website's <em>Band of the Month</em> page and this was done purely with CSS2.1 styling. Being a fluid site layout, the timeline bars' widths are fully fluid. You can see it in action on the <a href="demo-site/frame.html" title="Demo Website"><strong>demo website</strong></a></p>

